SUMMARY:Storytime at 1st Street Dining Commons
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy a special outdoor storytime hosted by the Beaverton Library in downtown Beaverton! Bring your little ones for stories\, songs\, and a relaxed morning of community at the Dining Commons. There will also be crafts and fun activities—all free! \nFamilies are welcome to stay after storytime to enjoy the space and explore downtown. \nWednesday\, March 25\n10:00–11:00 AM\nDining Commons | Downtown Beaverton \nPerfect for toddlers\, preschoolers\, and their caregivers.\nBring a blanket or small chairs for seating. \nHosted by the Beaverton City Library and the Beaverton Downtown Association. Part of the new Dining Commons Kids Series.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/storytime-at-1st-street-dining-commons/
LOCATION:1st Street Dining Commons\, SW Washington Ave &\, SW 1st St\, Beaverton\, OR 97005
CATEGORIES:Arts/Crafts,Books/Library,Educational,Kids Calendar,Outdoor
